BLUETONGUE - RUSSIA: ex GERMANY, LIVESTOCK, SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
******************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 20 Jan 2012
Source: Rosselkhoznadzor (Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance) [edited]
http://fsvps.ru/fsvps/news/4061.html?_language=en


Detection of cattle with bluetongue antibodies delivered from Germany in Kaluga Oblast
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Within monitoring activities the All-Russian Scientific and Research Institute for Veterinary Virology and Microbiology detected bluetongue seropositive cattle delivered from Germany to OOO "Kaluzhskaya Niva", settlement of Khokhlovka, Peremyshl' Rayon [district], Kaluga Oblast [region] last year [2011]. The number of seropositive cattle is 35 animals out of 57 delivered (61 percent).

As it was reported previously, bluetongue was detected in Smolensk Oblast also in animals exported from Germany. Due to this fact Sergey Dankvert, head of the Rosselkhoznadzor sent a letter to Paola Testori Coggi, director general of the Directorate-General for Health and Consumers of the European Commission. In it he expressed his deepest concern about this event and addressed to the EC a request to send EU veterinary experts to Russia for sampling blood from infected animals as soon as possible and to test these samples immediately in the World Reference Center for bluetongue in Pirbright Laboratory, United Kingdom.

The Rosselkhoznadzor request was not considered by the European Commission. The Rosselkhoznadzor is studying the current situation attentively and reserves the right to take any appropriate measures.

--
